Background.$description: Color applied to content behind scrollable content. Also used for the background of components that have no distinct container, such as Navigation Drawer.

Error.$description: Indicates errors and warning states in components such as text fields.

Error Container.$description: Background color used to display errors with less prominence.

Inverse On Surface.$description: Applied to content on top of inverseSurface.

Inverse Primary.$description: Action-color on inverted containers (e.g. the button on a SnackBar).

Inverse Surface.$description: Background for inverted components, such as SnackBars, that contrast against the regular surface.

On Background.$description: Applied to icons and text placed on top of background.

On Error.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of error.

On Error Container.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of errorContainer.

On Primary.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of primary.

On Primary Container.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of primaryContainer.

On Primary Fixed.$description: Applied to high-emphasis content on top of primaryFixed.

On Primary Fixed Variant.$description: Applied to lower-emphasis content on top of primaryFixed or primaryFixedDim.

On Secondary.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of secondary.

On Secondary Container.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of secondaryContainer.

On Secondary Fixed.$description: Applied to high-emphasis content on top of secondaryFixed.

On Secondary Fixed Variant.$description: Applied to lower-emphasis content on top of secondaryFixed or secondaryFixedDim.

On Surface.$description: Applied to text and icons on surface.

On Surface Variant.$description: Applied to icons and text on top of surfaceVariant. Lower emphasis than onSurface.

On Tertiary.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of tertiary.

On Tertiary Container.$description: Applied to content (icons, text) on top of tertiaryContainer.

On Tertiary Fixed.$description: Applied to high-emphasis content on top of tertiaryFixed.

On Tertiary Fixed Variant.$description: Applied to lower-emphasis content on top of tertiaryFixed or tertiaryFixedDim.

Outline.$description: Utility color for borders, outlines, and dividers that need sufficient contrast.

Outline Variant.$description: Utility color for decorative elements and dividers that require less emphasis.

Primary.$description: Key color used for prominent UI elements such as FABs, filled buttons, and active states.

Primary Container.$description: Softer background color used for components requiring less prominence than primary.

Primary Fixed.$description: A primary container color that remains fixed regardless of theme brightness.

Primary Fixed Dim.$description: A lower-emphasis primary container color, fixed regardless of theme brightness.

Scrim.$description: Color of the scrim overlay on screen content to prevent interaction.

Secondary.$description: Accent color used for components that have less emphasis than primary, such as filter chips.

Secondary Container.$description: Softer background color used for secondary-role containers.

Secondary Fixed.$description: A secondary container color that remains fixed regardless of theme brightness.

Secondary Fixed Dim.$description: A lower-emphasis secondary container color, fixed regardless of theme brightness.

Shadow.$description: Color of shadows cast by elevated components.

Surface.$description: Default color for component backgrounds. Also used as default container color for FAB, Chips, and similar elements.

Surface Bright.$description: A surface that always has a bright appearance.

Surface Dim.$description: A surface that always has a dim appearance.

Surface Tint.$description: Layered at various opacities on top of surfaces to represent elevation.

Surface Variant.$description: Alternative container color for lower emphasis compared to surface.

Tertiary.$description: Color used to balance primary and secondary colors, or bring attention to specific elements.

Tertiary Container.$description: Softer background color used for tertiary-role containers.

Tertiary Fixed.$description: A tertiary container color that remains fixed regardless of theme brightness.

Tertiary Fixed Dim.$description: A lower-emphasis tertiary container color, fixed regardless of theme brightness.
